article.headline: Texas Southern 52, Grambling 50
article.story: GRAMBLING, La. (AP) -- Sean Walker scored at the buzzer to lift Texas Southern to a 52-50 win over Grambling State on Saturday night. Allen Lovett led Texas Southern (7-7, 3-1 Southwestern Athletic Conference) with 22 points including 8-of-10 free throw attempts and six rebounds. Walker added 10 points, five rebounds, two assists, two steals and two blocked shots. Texas Southern shot only 33 percent (18-of-55) from the floor while going 0-of-7 from the 3-point range. Paul Haynes and Brion Rush each had 13 points apiece while pulling down seven and eight rebounds respectively for Grambling (4-11, 2-3). Texas Southern outscored Grambling 30-12 in the paint. Grambling shot only 32 percent from the floor (18-of-56) and 25 percent (6-of-24) from the 3-point range. Grambling led 25-22 at halftime.
